prompt:
Add a public function called ClampValue to Contracts.calr that clamps a value between min and max. It takes i32 parameters min, max, and value and returns i32. Use multiple preconditions and postconditions.

Use this exact Calor multiple contracts syntax:
§F{f001:ClampValue:pub}
  §I{i32:min}
  §I{i32:max}
  §I{i32:value}
  §O{i32}
  §Q (<= min max)
  §Q (>= max min)
  §S (>= result min)
  §S (<= result max)
  §S (-> (and (>= value min) (<= value max)) (== result value))
  §R (? (< value min) min (? (> value max) max value))
§/F{f001}

Multiple contracts:
- Multiple §Q lines define multiple preconditions (all must hold)
- Multiple §S lines define multiple postconditions (all must hold)
- Each contract focuses on one aspect of correctness
